<item>
            <title>[LU-17175] Explore possibility to start lsvcgssd from l_getauth</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17175</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Explore the possibility for &lt;tt&gt;l_getauth&lt;/tt&gt; to start the &lt;tt&gt;lsvcgssd&lt;/tt&gt; daemon if it&apos;s not running yet. For SSK, daemon startup time is much longer than with Kerberos, because of sk_speedtest_dh_valid(). So to avoid hitting the upcall timeout, we could use predefined default values to save time in this particular case.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
